---
import Section from './Section.astro';
import SectionHeader from './SectionHeader.astro';
---

<Section>

  <SectionHeader
    eyebrow="Before You Start"
    title="Think About Your Character First"
    maxWidth="lg"
  />

  <div class="mt-8 max-w-3xl">

    <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-300">
      Before using these prompts, think about your character.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-300">
      You don't need every detail.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-300">
      Even a simple idea like
      <span class="text-white font-medium">"A retired knight hunting monsters."</span>
      or
      <span class="text-white font-medium">"A cyberpunk detective."</span>
      is enough.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-300">
      The Character Blueprint prompt will intelligently fill the missing information while keeping everything visually consistent.
    </p>

  </div>

</Section>